We’re having a hard time with the VH-109.

We have successfully updated the firmware to 1.2.6. We are able to access the radios configuration page via an ethernet cable to the DS port, but the Driver Station is not showing any communications. We also cannot deploy code. We have configured our team number and passwords for the networks, and we have DIP switch #3 set to ON. We are able to connect to the 2.4 Ghz network with our laptop, but it yields the same results as ethernet to DS.

The Driver Station is showing link-bad, DS radio(.4)-bad, robot radio(.1)-GOOD, roboRIO(.2)-bad, FMS-bad
It is also saying in green “Radio Version: ”

We have no other VH-109 or VH-113, so using those as access points is not an option.

What options do we have? Am I missing something huge? Thanks!
